<br>
I love your website BTW. I had lots of fun poking around the various threads! <br>
<br>
I have a friend who plays a 48th level Rogue - bound in FV and currently hunting in CoM. He would like to help me complete this quest now. I know that he can turn in gems to get bottles (for the life of me, I cant recall the NPC's name that hands out the quest...) I am hoping SOMEONE here has successfully competed the quest using this method, and can shed some light on how to go about it.<br>
<br>
Ther used to be a spoiler marked ALTERNATE: Using a 1'st level Rogue in CoM, on Graffe's but the link doesn't work right now / anymore.<br>
<br>
1) How does the Rogue identify which bottle is which?<br>
<br>
2) Is there an optimum route or path the Rogue HAS to take to complete the TURN in and get back out in relative safety?<br>
<br>
3) Does MQ work like every other MQ. He hands in the CoM and KC portions - FIRST. Then I hand in TT portion and get the SPELL?<br>
<br>
Your thoughts? Many thanks!<br>
<br>
<br>
