<br>
Direct your friend to my page at <!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://how.to/stayhidden">how.to/stayhidden</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--> for details. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/uyalum.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Yalum</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(12/3/01 5:29:02 am)</font><br>     <br>Community Supporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: City of Mist: Can a Rogue use Hide + Sneak to MQ Wiz spe</span><hr size=1> You're still going to have to fight your way up there, any rogue who tried solo would be eaten by goos.  This would be an alternative to having a chanter charm him, though. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/ulenadaynastardew.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Lenadayna Stardew</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(12/3/01 5:09:57 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: City of Mist: Can a Rogue use Hide + Sneak to MQ Wiz spe</span><hr size=1>    No idea, but rogues generally don't feature into any part of this quest and the wizard's focus on making this quest easier for the level it is intened (read: actually possible), is getting this skeleton moved.<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/uprodigious.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Prodigious</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Safehouse Supporter</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(12/4/01 2:48:46 pm)</font><br>     <br>Community Supporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: City of Mist: Can a Rogue use Hide + Sneak to MQ Wiz spe</span><hr size=1> my thoughts....<br>
<br>
are you evil or good? how's the rogue's venrilsathir faction? the rogue, and you, needs amiable or better faction with VenrilSathir (outpost in OT) to do the quest there, not sure what you need to do it in FV.<br>
<br>
identify can be cast on anyone, just hold the item on your cursor and have it cast on you.<br>
<br>
I think CoM is pretty safe from stuff seeing rogue hide, but right opposite of the room with the skeleton (which btw is a rare spawn - might need to spend hours clearing PH's) is another random mob, who will see the rogue right as he opens trade window with the skeleton. you might be able to do it fast enough (click trade really fast), but I dunno. <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/uprodigious.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Prodigious</A> at: 12/4/01 2:49:33 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/uizmaeleq.showPublicProfile?language=EN>IzmaelEQ</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(12/4/01 3:22:10 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: City of Mist: Can a Rogue use Hide + Sneak to MQ Wiz spe</span><hr size=1> The only stuff that sees rogue hide fairly consistently is the goos.  About 1 out of 4 goo's see rogue hide.  But then quite often you can wait until that goo walks (?) away or, if you're high level enough, sometimes you can just run by and they won't attack.<br>
<br>
On a side note, I'm used to open the locked doors by holding the lockpicks on the mouse cursor, and pressing the &quot;U&quot; key, rather than clicking the door.  You never know whether the EQ engine would rather decide that you're trying to give the lockpicks to a mob behind the door =) <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/uhonourtruestrike.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Honour Truestrike</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(12/5/01 4:47:38 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: City of Mist: Can a Rogue use Hide + Sneak to MQ Wiz spe</span><hr size=1> Interesting to know about the goos. I've only ever had one see through hide/sneak and it was a goo on the first ramp up - the crystal one. Even the reavers don't see through, I love that zone, hehe. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/ucore1024.showPublicProfile?language=EN>core1024</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(12/5/01 9:27:35 am)</font><br>     <br>Community Supporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: City of Mist: Can a Rogue use Hide + Sneak to MQ Wiz spe</span><hr size=1> If there aren't any see-invis goos in the way you could do as was suggested for the KC low level rogue turn in; make sure you do everything fast, since you're going to die as soon as you do the turn in, and then either drag your corpse out or get it summoned; I'd suggest levelling the rogue to level 6 so you have some time either way.<br>
